<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>INTERNATIONAL</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/04/international/asia/04AFGH.html?todaysheadlines">U.S. Planes Pound Enemy as Troops Face Tough Fight</a></b><br>
Allied ground forces met fierce resistance Sunday as they tried to seal off escape routes from one of the last Taliban and Al Qaeda refuges.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/04/international/middleeast/04MIDE.html?todaysheadlines">Latest Attacks Stun Israelis and Dampen Hopes for Peace</a></b><br>
More killings Sunday put a damper on hopes   that were raised in some quarters by a Saudi peace proposal for the Middle East.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/04/international/americas/04COLO.html?todaysheadlines">Colombian Rebels Step Up Pace and Intensity of Attacks</a></b><br>
Peace talks collapsed just 11 days ago, and it took no time at all for Colombia to plunge into a new, ominous phase of the long-running conflict.
<P>
</font>













<p>
<a href="http://www.nytimes.com/pages/world/index.html?todaysheadline">MORE INTERNATIONAL NEWS</a>
