<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>TECHNOLOGY</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/04/technology/04HEWL.html?todaysheadlines">Former Chief of Hewlett Urges Rejection of Merger</a></b><br>
Lewis E. Platt visited an influential shareholder advisory firm, Institutional Shareholder Services, last week to explain why he is against the deal Carleton S. Fiorina has championed.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/04/technology/04GLOB.html?todaysheadlines">A Rival Offer Is Expected for Global</a></b><br>
A Los Angeles investment firm that specializes in corporate turnarounds is likely to make an offer this week for Global Crossing, the beleaguered communications company.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/04/arts/design/04ARTS.html?todaysheadlines">If You Can't Join 'Em, You Can Always Tweak 'Em</a></b><br>
An artist recently registered the Web address WhitneyBiennial.com and on it he's posted his own opinions of the perpetually controversial exhibit.
<P>
</font>













<p>
