<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>OP-ED </b></font><br>






<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/04/opinion/04SAFI.html?todaysheadlines">The Inspection Ploy</a></b>
<br>
By WILLIAM SAFIRE
<br>
Saddam Hussein has restarted the business of postponing an attack on his regime by the United States until he can  finish making weapons of mass destruction.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/04/opinion/04HERB.html?todaysheadlines">A Different City</a></b>
<br>
By BOB HERBERT
<br>
New York is a much different place than it was in  the summer of 1997 when Abner Louima was hideously attacked by police officers in the 70th Precinct station house in Brooklyn.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/04/opinion/04GRAN.html?todaysheadlines">Bargains Everywhere but on Wall Street</a></b>
<br>
By JAMES GRANT
<br>
The stock market peaked two years  ago. Yet the investment merchandise  remains prohibitively expensive.
<P>
</font>









